metadata.name: кคɭєเ๔๏ร - Շгเคภﻮɭє #203
metadata.description:
My genesis piece is an exploration of the Penrose triangle. As Escher knew, it is an addictive shape and I have used it as the base for my beloved kaleidoscopes.
Each triangle will have 6 different traits with different levels of rarity.
The last trait is called Special and includes 9 ultra-rare effects.

At each click the triangles will regenerate based on the traits they have inherited.

There are 492 different color palettes + 10 custom made palettes provided by some artists and friends. Each custom palette has a 0.3% probability of getting picked.

A big thank you for the custom palettes goes to:
Yuri @p_e_p_p @shig_nft @PureSpider @HarveyMcFly @Flygohr @ChrisRandallAr1 @007_shank @oonthinice

To my dad.

Yours,
CDB

metadata.name: Pobbles #224
metadata.description:
The pobbles are generative blob-rocks: staring in silence, sometimes half-smiling, generally bored. 

• The pobbles are digital recreations of a series of rock-doodles by S.F.Kislev (my big brother). They are an attempt to capture a specific, singular handwriting, and evolve it using code. 
• See the original, 2014 handmade version here - https://pobbles.tez.page..
• Alternative titles considered include Peggles™, Plops™, Blobbies™, Floofs™, Flintstones™, Lardies™, Plumps™, Fats™ and Wet-Ones™. 
• The pobbles are written entirely in paper.js and p5.js. 
• The pobbles are an effort to take generative art into the realm of the cute. 
• They work well with toddlers.

🖨️ Collectors minting at the first auction tier receive a hand-crafted riso print of their pobble. Color variation between the file and the print will apply. 🖨️

metadata.name: Cables and Clouds #123
metadata.description:
Capturing clouds... an old dream of mad scientist... coming true...
But wait... are they real clouds ? Maybe... maybe not...
Is it the real life ?
Is this just fantasy ?

Interaction.
Press h in live mode to list the possibilities.
Key 's'  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key 'c' to change color palette
Key 'd' to toggle a special color mode to highlight the different components (and have the number of points used in your specific drawing).

Features.
18 different features displayed (format, color palettes, main elements characteristics, rare elements...).

metadata.name: Traveler #29
metadata.description:
Retro sci-fi style landscape sketch drawn by code.

Features:
- Terrain: Cliff, Cavern, Sky, Megalopolis, Desert, Sea, Space, Volcano
- Orientation: Landscape, Portlait
- Palette: White, Cream, Tan, Pink, Green, Yellow, Orange
- Background: Light, Dark

Live view options:
- Press "s" key: Saves the high resolution image (4200 x 3300 for landscape, 3300 x 4200 for portlait)

Depending on the device you run it on, it may take some time for the drawing to complete.
Made with p5js.

June 2022
ykxotkx
